%N A396465 Consider the square spiral in a single quadrant with its cells numbered starting at 0. Three players take turns and place black knights(K), cyan antelopes(A), and red ferzes(F), respectively, at the smallest unoccupied cell not attacked by an existing pieces of a different color. Sequence lists unoccupied squares.
%C A396465 A variant of A392177 with three players with different fairy chess pieces.
%H A396465 Sander G. Huisman, <a href="/A396465/b396465.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A396465 Brady Haran, Jonas Karlsson, and N. J. A. Sloane, <a href="https://youtu.be/UiX4CFIiegM">Red & Black Knights (extraordinary result)</a>;<a href="https://youtu.be/VgmDuBCayPw">Amazing Chessboard Patterns (extra)</a>, YouTube Numberphile videos, May 2026
%H A396465 Sander G. Huisman, <a href="/A396465/a396465.png">Image of the first 10^5 grid positions.</a>
%H A396465 Sander G. Huisman, <a href="/A396465/a396465_1.png">Image of the first 10^6 grid positions.</a>
%H A396465 Sander G. Huisman, <a href="/A396465/a396465_2.png">Image of the first 10^7 grid positions.</a>
%H A396465 Sander G. Huisman, <a href="/A396465/a396465_3.png">Image of the first 10^8 grid positions.</a>
%e A396465 The grid is as follows:
%e A396465   0  1  8  9  24 25
%e A396465   3  2  7  10 23 26
%e A396465   4  5  6  11 22 27
%e A396465   15 14 13 12 21 .
%e A396465   16 17 18 19 20 .
%e A396465   .  .  .  .  .  .
%e A396465 And gets occupied as follows:
%e A396465   K A . A . K
%e A396465   K F K K . A
%e A396465   F K . A K .
%e A396465   A . F K . A
%e A396465   . F K F A K
%e A396465   . A . F . F
%e A396465 Where the . means that the position remains unoccupied.
%Y A396465 Cf. A392182, A392183. Pieces given by: A396461, A396462, A396463.
